OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCalls to drop 'unfair' tax 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fon period pants            
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Two major retailers of period pants are
OL,6, calling for them to be VAT-free in line
OL,7, with other sanitary products.          
OL,9,FMarks & Spencer and WUKA have been     
OL,10,Fjoined by politicians and environmental
OL,11,Fgroups urging the government to act.   
OL,13,FCurrently period pants, which are      
OL,14,Fabsorbent, washable and reusable, are  
OL,15,Fclassified as garments and VAT is      
OL,16,Flevied at 20%.                         
OL,18,FBut other period products such as pads,
OL,19,Ftampons and reusable menstrual cups    
OL,20,Fhave been exempt since 2021.           
